radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild dependent atelectasis at the lung bases; multiple small rounded hypodensities in the liver, with the largest measuring 9 mm likely representing a cyst; normal gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands; multiple bilateral renal cysts; borderline dilated loops of small bowel with air-fluid levels; abnormal appendix with calcific densities and extensive periappendiceal inflammatory changes; small amount of free fluid in the right lower quadrant and pelvis; no osseous lesions suspicious for malignancy.
